<br>
fair flower of felwithe, i would like to respectfully disagree with you.  to call the vox/naggy raids as &quot;pick up&quot; raids is an oversimplification.  some people use that term to describe any raid that is not a guild raid.  as an example, sage/torm's raids are still described as pick up raids but are better run than some guild raids i've been on.  <br>
<br>
having never been on one, you are missing one point.  as was voiced by theo, the naggy/vox &quot;community&quot; to a large degree has developed certain practices and viewpoints.  you will find this in any group.  one of the views (although not shared by all, especially the greedy or the new) for palys is that it's &quot;right&quot; to put in your time.  PERSONALLY (and i have heard several other paladins say the same thing) they dont mind &quot;paying your dues 46 - 49&quot;.  as mentioned, it's almost viewed as a right of passage.  <br>
<br>
i hope this doesnt sound as if i'm saying you have no room to speak since you havent done a naggy/vox raid.  i'm only saying that if you had gone on some of the raids you may have received the same impression i had (if the attitude/ views of your contemporaries were the same). <br>
<br>
no, no one ever sat down and wrote this down.  this is not a consipiracy.  it is what has evolved and how we as paladins have justified in our minds the tedious wait for a paly book.  i'm not even bringing the &quot;waiting at 52lvl&quot; aspect of it into this.  and my statements above are not blanket statements for all pallys, not even for all pallys that attend the raids.  it's just my impression of how i and some of the paladins whom i've raided with feel, or been conditioned to view the situation.<br>
<br>
personally, i dont have a problem with a 52 paly who has gone to a lot of raids getting the book over me by default.  you are right, those 46 to 49 are often the difference in defeating naggy/vox.  but again, for some of us, it's a part of the framework by which we view our rp aspect of what a paladin is.  service to the greater good.  i know that sounds corny and insincere on my part, but it is how i view it.  <br>
<br>
and no, i dont think jex's actions are designed to appear altruistic while secretly serving her friends.  as was commented by theo (i think) her rules favor ALL 52 paladins not just the ones she knows.  obviously, if she gets a lot of palys signing up she can pick her friends and thus she would be rewarding them, but again, if a paly has put in the time and effort into supporting raids, then they should be rewarded.  yes, i can see where it might appear unfair, but i think the paly book going to the highest level paly in the raid is comparable to NBG.  some people claim NBG is not fair since certain classes who risked may not be rewarded.  <br>
<br>
not to sound holier than anyone, but in response to some who argue about an epic that isnt even that good, yes, it's not &quot;worth the effort&quot;.  but i think some of us palys want it for the same reason we picked to play a paladin.  god knows it wasnt to play an uber class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
