<br>
I for one don't mind attending raids where the epic loot is defaulted or restricted.  If some paladin has gone to 10 naggy raids and not gotten a book, maybe they deserve to get one the next raid.  But if I'm attending a raid, I think it's fair for me to expect anyone who'll be getting loot to have put in some sort of substantial effort toward killing the beast.  This excludes people who are there to kill giants or people who's levels are so low they get evaporated within 5 seconds of the fight starting.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
